        'One important limitation of image resizing is that enlarging an image beyond its original dimensions reduces quality. Upscaling adds pixels through interpolation, which produces visible blurring. Downsizing has almost no quality impact, but avoid upscaling whenever possible and instead source a higher-resolution original.',
